WEBVTT

00:00.015 --> 00:01.265
<i>Previously on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.439 --> 00:02.876
You hung me out to dry.

00:02.976 --> 00:04.460
How exactly did I do that?

00:04.560 --> 00:05.842
By making it seem like
I'm the one

00:05.895 --> 00:07.194
that's taking away
your dream wedding.

00:07.229 --> 00:08.929
You are the one taking away
my dream wedding!

00:08.964 --> 00:09.930
We're getting married,

00:09.965 --> 00:12.065
and it can be as small
as possible

00:12.101 --> 00:13.600
with just our close friends,
okay?

00:13.636 --> 00:15.135
I think we should consider
promoting Jack Soloff

00:15.170 --> 00:16.837
to name partner.
Are you crazy?

00:16.872 --> 00:17.971
Hardman's got something
on him.

00:18.007 --> 00:19.373
If Hardman has something
on him,

00:19.408 --> 00:21.108
then we need to have it
on him, too.

00:21.143 --> 00:23.944
You want me gone,
call for a vote,

00:23.979 --> 00:26.179
'cause we know what's going on
with Daniel's investor,

00:26.215 --> 00:28.282
and Harvey's about to put a stop
to it right now.

00:28.317 --> 00:29.850
Why should I believe you
would even live up to

00:29.885 --> 00:31.051
your end of the bargain?

00:31.053 --> 00:32.552
Because I don't give a shit

00:32.588 --> 00:34.221
about your war with
Daniel Hardman.

00:34.256 --> 00:37.257
All I want to do is see you
get down on your knees

00:37.293 --> 00:39.793
and say, "I quit."

00:39.795 --> 00:41.395
You're breaking the law
every day.

00:41.430 --> 00:43.063
Oh, so now I shouldn't
get married?

00:43.065 --> 00:44.131
I'm saying you should quit.

00:44.166 --> 00:46.066
The longer you go,

00:46.101 --> 00:47.301
the less the money matters.

00:47.336 --> 00:48.602
You almost got caught,
didn't you?

00:48.637 --> 00:50.003
I went to talk to someone.

00:50.039 --> 00:51.271
Who?

00:51.307 --> 00:53.340
You know who.

00:54.343 --> 00:58.211
Mom?
Dad!

01:00.015 --> 01:01.698
Grammy, what are you
doing here?

01:01.734 --> 01:03.567
Where's mom?
I want to give her a hug.

01:03.619 --> 01:05.152
Dad, too.

01:05.187 --> 01:06.603
What?

01:06.655 --> 01:08.789
You told me not to be mad
at them last night, remember?

01:08.824 --> 01:10.390
You said once they got home
I should tell them I was sorry

01:10.392 --> 01:11.992
and give them a hug.

01:12.027 --> 01:14.995
But they didn't wake me up,
so I didn't get to,

01:15.030 --> 01:18.165
and I want to.

01:18.200 --> 01:20.200
Michael, I have to
tell you something.

01:20.235 --> 01:22.769
What is it?

01:22.805 --> 01:26.139
Your--your parents,

01:26.175 --> 01:31.228
last night they were in
a car accident.

01:31.263 --> 01:36.149
But they're gonna
be okay, right?

01:36.185 --> 01:40.153
Michael, they passed away.

01:40.189 --> 01:42.939
What?

01:42.992 --> 01:44.408
No.

01:44.443 --> 01:46.943
No, they can't be.

01:46.996 --> 01:48.528
You're wrong!

01:48.580 --> 01:49.863
<font color="#D900D9">[cries]</font>

01:49.865 --> 01:52.032
I wish I were, baby.

01:52.034 --> 01:53.617
I wish I...

01:53.669 --> 01:56.036
Why didn't you
wake me up?

01:56.038 --> 01:57.371
I could have gone
to the hospital.

01:57.373 --> 01:59.373
I could have seen them!

01:59.425 --> 02:01.758
They didn't make it to
the hospital, sweetheart,

02:01.794 --> 02:05.429
and--and I didn't want to
tell you until I had to.

02:05.464 --> 02:07.214
How could you
do this to me?

02:07.216 --> 02:08.632
How could you not wake me up?

02:08.684 --> 02:11.635
<i><font color="#D900D9">[soul music]</font></i>

02:11.687 --> 02:19.693
<i>♪
♪</i>

