02:57.349 --> 02:59.983
Hey.

03:00.018 --> 03:01.151
Hey.

03:01.186 --> 03:02.736
<font color="#D900D9">[clears throat]</font>

03:02.771 --> 03:04.354
What are you doing up
so early?

03:04.406 --> 03:06.857
Oh, nothing, just going
through this old box of stuff.

03:06.909 --> 03:08.275
Does that have
something to do with

03:08.277 --> 03:10.994
you seeing Trevor last night?

03:11.029 --> 03:13.163
Yeah.
Yeah, it does.

03:13.198 --> 03:14.915
Is he still a mess?

03:14.950 --> 03:16.833
No. No, he's actually
doing really well.

03:16.869 --> 03:18.285
So what do you mean?

03:18.320 --> 03:20.253
I mean,
I need to take the day.

03:20.289 --> 03:21.788
You need to
take the day?

03:21.824 --> 03:23.290
- Yeah.
- Is there something wrong?

03:23.342 --> 03:25.992
No, nothing's wrong.

03:26.044 --> 03:28.061
Just got something
I need to do.

03:28.097 --> 03:30.230
Okay.

03:31.867 --> 03:33.333
<i><font color="#D900D9">[elevator bell dings]</font></i>

03:37.523 --> 03:39.489
Jessica.

03:39.525 --> 03:40.874
Jack.

03:40.909 --> 03:43.360
Did you reconsider my offer?

03:43.412 --> 03:44.494
About resigning?

03:44.546 --> 03:47.030
Yeah, no, not a chance.

03:47.082 --> 03:51.384
But the bylaws require you
to be given formal notice so...

03:54.573 --> 03:55.522
You're calling for

03:55.557 --> 03:56.990
an emergency
vote of no confidence today?

03:57.025 --> 03:58.191
Yes.

03:58.227 --> 03:59.876
Well, you're shitty
at math, Jack,

03:59.912 --> 04:01.728
because even if
we lost McKernon,

04:01.763 --> 04:04.431
one client is not enough to
turn the partners against me.

04:04.466 --> 04:06.066
Check your calculator,
Jessica,

04:06.101 --> 04:07.651
because you only had
half the partners,

04:07.686 --> 04:09.369
and every single one of them
is about to lose

04:09.404 --> 04:11.655
the biggest client to
a hostile takeover

04:11.690 --> 04:13.840
because of
your poor leadership.

04:13.876 --> 04:15.809
We both know the only
hostile takeover you care about

04:15.844 --> 04:17.344
is the one in here.

04:17.379 --> 04:19.045
Take a picture,

04:19.081 --> 04:23.450
because tomorrow morning,
those letters are coming down.

04:23.485 --> 04:26.336
<i><font color="#D900D9">[tense music]</font></i>

04:26.388 --> 04:34.327
<i>♪
♪</i>

04:35.581 --> 04:36.963
Where the hell is he?

04:37.015 --> 04:38.532
I don't know.

04:38.567 --> 04:40.867
Gretchen, I swear, if you
want to have a job tomorrow,

04:40.869 --> 04:42.536
you better tell me
where Harvey is.

04:42.588 --> 04:46.373
Ms. Pearson, every Sunday
I lay out all my outfits

04:46.375 --> 04:48.875
for the coming week,
and I have no intention

04:48.927 --> 04:51.178
of not wearing one of
those babies tomorrow.

04:51.213 --> 04:53.763
So with all due respect,

04:53.799 --> 04:55.432
I don't know.

04:55.467 --> 04:58.718
Well, if you want to pick out
your clothes for next week,

04:58.770 --> 05:00.854
you better find the hell out.

05:02.357 --> 05:06.026
<i>♪ See the money,</i>
<i>wanna stay for your meal ♪</i>

05:06.061 --> 05:09.362
<i>♪ Get another piece of pie</i>
<i>for your wife ♪</i>

05:09.398 --> 05:12.532
<i>♪ Everybody wanna know</i>
<i>how it feel ♪</i>

05:12.568 --> 05:16.286
♪ Everybody wanna see
<i>what it's like ♪</i>

05:16.321 --> 05:19.206
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
<i>I don't mind ♪</i>

05:19.241 --> 05:23.210
♪ Me and Missy is
<i>so busy, busy making money ♪</i>

05:23.245 --> 05:24.661
<i>♪ All right ♪</i>

05:24.713 --> 05:28.713
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Suits 5x10 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Faith</font>
