05:28.751 --> 05:30.051
♪ All step back,
<i>I'm 'bout to dance ♪</i>

05:30.052 --> 05:31.384
<i>♪ The greenback boogie ♪</i>

05:31.408 --> 05:33.408
== sync, corrected by <font color=#00FF00>elderman</font> ==
<font color=#00FFFF>@elder_man</font>

05:33.844 --> 05:35.750
Harvey.
Harvey, wait.

05:35.850 --> 05:37.935
Wait.
I-I made a mistake.

05:38.035 --> 05:39.868
Don't you touch me.

05:39.904 --> 05:41.520
You don't understand.

05:41.555 --> 05:43.489
I understand you made a fool
out of Dad for the last time.

05:43.541 --> 05:44.990
Lily, let me try.
Harvey--

05:44.992 --> 05:46.558
You get the hell out of
my father's house.

05:46.594 --> 05:47.594
Bobby, get--get out.

05:47.628 --> 05:50.162
Get out!

05:50.164 --> 05:51.680
Listen, Harvey to me.

05:51.715 --> 05:53.165
No, you don't know
what you're doing.

05:53.200 --> 05:54.399
I know exactly
what I'm doing.

05:54.435 --> 05:56.902
Harvey, think about what
it would do to your father.

05:56.937 --> 05:58.670
To Marcus.
It'll kill them.

05:58.706 --> 06:00.539
You said that once before
and you'd never do this again.

06:00.574 --> 06:01.840
I know what I said.

06:01.876 --> 06:03.575
And I said if you did
I'd tell him everything,

06:03.611 --> 06:04.543
and I'm going to.

06:04.578 --> 06:05.494
Harvey, I am begging you.

06:05.546 --> 06:07.513
Don't tear us all to pieces.

06:07.548 --> 06:09.314
Don't destroy your family.

06:09.350 --> 06:12.050
Don't you dare
put this shit on me.

06:12.086 --> 06:13.218
<i><font color="#D900D9">[door slams]</font></i>

06:14.421 --> 06:17.089
Harvey?

06:17.124 --> 06:18.724
Where did you just go?

06:18.759 --> 06:19.892
I'm sorry.

06:19.927 --> 06:21.643
I was just thinking about
the time I had to decide

06:21.695 --> 06:23.061
whether or not
I should tell my father

06:23.063 --> 06:24.296
that my mother was
cheating on him.

06:24.331 --> 06:25.864
And maybe we should
talk about that.

06:25.900 --> 06:27.266
I didn't come here
to talk about that.

06:27.268 --> 06:29.368
I came here to figure out
whether or not I should resign.

06:29.403 --> 06:31.336
And then you started
thinking about your mother.

06:31.372 --> 06:32.805
And if your brain went
to the one,

06:32.840 --> 06:34.640
then it's connecting it
to the other,

06:34.675 --> 06:36.074
and the best thing
we can do right now

06:36.110 --> 06:37.176
is to try and figure out why.

06:37.211 --> 06:38.277
I don't have time
for that.

06:38.312 --> 06:39.812
Harvey, you asked me
to block out the day

06:39.847 --> 06:42.347
for an emergency session,
and I did.

06:42.383 --> 06:44.416
We have time.

06:47.588 --> 06:49.471
The white ones are best.

06:49.507 --> 06:51.690
You're just here to
make me go in.

06:51.742 --> 06:54.026
I am.

06:54.061 --> 06:55.561
Because sometimes
we make choices

06:55.596 --> 06:57.262
we're not old enough to make,

06:57.298 --> 06:59.298
and then we regret them.

06:59.333 --> 07:01.266
I don't want that
to happen to you.

07:01.302 --> 07:03.468
Why would I regret
not going into that place?

07:03.504 --> 07:05.037
'Cause it's a chance to
say good-bye to your parents.

07:05.072 --> 07:06.438
I already missed that.

07:06.473 --> 07:07.372
<font color="#D900D9">[grunts]</font>

07:07.408 --> 07:09.074
<i><font color="#D900D9">[rock lands]</font></i>

07:09.109 --> 07:11.710
Mike.

07:11.745 --> 07:14.179
Sometimes when people
lose someone they love,

07:14.181 --> 07:15.814
they get mad at them.

07:15.850 --> 07:17.766
I'm not mad at them.

07:17.801 --> 07:19.885
I'm mad at God.

07:19.920 --> 07:23.055
I understand
you're mad at God.

07:23.090 --> 07:25.891
Maybe you're even
mad at me, too.

07:25.926 --> 07:30.078
But I came out here
to give you something.

07:30.114 --> 07:31.363
St. William,

07:31.415 --> 07:33.282
patron saint of orphans.

07:33.334 --> 07:34.666
You know who this is.

07:34.702 --> 07:35.834
I know who
all the saints are,

07:35.870 --> 07:37.252
and I don't want it.

07:37.288 --> 07:39.588
I don't want to be
an orphan.

07:39.623 --> 07:41.790
Then don't take it.

07:41.842 --> 07:43.792
<i><font color="#D900D9">[poignant music]</font></i>

07:43.844 --> 07:46.762
Because the truth is,
orphans are alone,

07:46.797 --> 07:50.849
and you're not.

07:50.885 --> 07:52.551
But not going in there

07:52.603 --> 07:54.887
isn't gonna change
what happened.

07:54.939 --> 07:58.557
And right now,
your grandmother needs you.

07:58.609 --> 08:00.726
But if you stay out here,

08:00.778 --> 08:03.028
she's gonna have to
face today alone.

08:03.063 --> 08:11.069
<i>♪
♪</i>

08:16.327 --> 08:24.333
<i>♪
♪</i>

08:32.809 --> 08:34.643
Well, it's official, Harvey.

08:34.678 --> 08:37.095
My fingers are way too old.

08:37.097 --> 08:38.429
Like hell.

08:38.482 --> 08:39.982
You can still outplay anyone.

08:40.017 --> 08:41.265
<font color="#D900D9">[chuckles]</font>

08:41.268 --> 08:43.268
You're a terrible liar.

08:43.270 --> 08:45.153
But I got to admit,

08:45.189 --> 08:49.908
I do love seeing my boy
in the crowd.

08:49.944 --> 08:51.310
Actually, Dad,
there's something

08:51.345 --> 08:53.028
I wanted to talk
to you about.

08:53.063 --> 08:55.080
I got something for you, too.
It's important.

08:55.115 --> 08:57.249
The band's splitting up.

08:57.284 --> 08:58.583
What?

08:58.636 --> 09:00.552
Lenny says he wants to spend
his golden years with Marge,

09:00.587 --> 09:02.220
and Dave's wrist isn't
getting any better, so--

09:02.256 --> 09:03.522
Well, what about Harry?

09:03.524 --> 09:05.057
Harry's already got an offer
from another group.

09:05.092 --> 09:06.558
Well, if they'll take him,
they'll take you.

09:06.593 --> 09:07.926
<font color="#D900D9">[laughs]</font>

09:07.962 --> 09:09.161
You're not listening, Harvey.

09:09.196 --> 09:11.897
I don't want them to take me.

09:11.932 --> 09:12.898
I want to come home.

09:12.933 --> 09:14.733
Dad, music is your life.

09:14.768 --> 09:17.135
Look, Harvey, I'm the same age
your grandfather was

09:17.171 --> 09:18.637
when he died,

09:18.672 --> 09:20.038
and I've already spent
way too much of my life

09:20.074 --> 09:21.373
away from my family.

09:21.408 --> 09:23.575
Don't start that.
You've been a great father.

09:23.610 --> 09:27.779
Maybe the cool father,
but...not a great one.

09:27.815 --> 09:30.449
And now, I know it's too late
to make that up to you.

09:30.484 --> 09:33.352
I'm just hoping it's not too
late to make it up to Marcus.

09:33.387 --> 09:35.053
Anyway, that's my news.

09:35.089 --> 09:38.290
What--what did you want
to talk about?

09:38.342 --> 09:40.125
Nothing.
I met a girl.

09:40.160 --> 09:41.927
Great.
What's her name?

09:41.962 --> 09:44.096
Scottie.

09:44.131 --> 09:46.465
I'm just trying to figure out
the long distance thing.

09:46.500 --> 09:48.717
All I can tell you there is,
if she's the one,

09:48.752 --> 09:52.738
you'll know, just like with
me and your mother.

09:55.409 --> 09:56.675
So you didn't tell him?

09:56.710 --> 09:57.976
No, I didn't.

09:58.012 --> 10:00.562
But you said that was the
night you decided to tell him.

10:00.597 --> 10:01.947
That was the night
I decided.

10:01.982 --> 10:04.583
No, you said it as though
it was all one night.

10:04.618 --> 10:08.420
I told you it was
all one night

10:08.472 --> 10:11.790
because I'm so used to lying
whenever I tell this story.

10:11.825 --> 10:12.858
My age--

10:12.860 --> 10:14.092
Why do you lie?

10:14.128 --> 10:16.428
Because I was a grown man
when it happened,

10:16.463 --> 10:17.623
and grown men
keep their words

10:17.648 --> 10:19.231
when they say
they're gonna do something,

10:19.233 --> 10:20.532
not give in to weakness.

10:20.584 --> 10:23.535
But it wasn't weakness that
made you break your word.

10:23.570 --> 10:24.936
It was love for your father.

10:24.972 --> 10:27.205
Then aren't I an asshole?

10:27.241 --> 10:30.792
Because I ended up ruining
everything two weeks later.

10:32.796 --> 10:34.880
Louis, I need to
talk to you for a minute.

10:34.915 --> 10:35.847
About what?

10:35.849 --> 10:37.215
Jack Soloff is
calling for a vote

10:37.251 --> 10:40.969
to remove me as
managing partner today.

10:41.004 --> 10:42.220
What?

10:42.222 --> 10:43.455
Why the hell would he do that

10:43.490 --> 10:44.856
after you offered to make him
name partner?

10:44.908 --> 10:46.708
Because I didn't offer
to make him name partner.

10:46.744 --> 10:48.060
I told him to resign.

10:48.095 --> 10:49.061
What happened to our plan?

10:49.096 --> 10:50.362
It wasn't our plan, Louis.

10:50.364 --> 10:52.230
It was your insane idea,

10:52.266 --> 10:53.398
and I was never
going to do it.

10:53.434 --> 10:54.366
Jessica--

10:54.401 --> 10:56.301
No, you listen to me.

10:56.336 --> 10:57.936
The matter at hand is

10:57.971 --> 11:00.005
making sure that we have
more people on our side

11:00.007 --> 11:01.773
than he and Daniel have
on theirs.

11:01.809 --> 11:03.141
What am I
supposed to do now?

11:03.177 --> 11:04.843
<i>You are going to do exactly</i>
<i>what I told you to do</i>

11:04.878 --> 11:05.994
<i>in the first place.</i>

11:06.046 --> 11:07.546
You're gonna find out
what Daniel has

11:07.581 --> 11:11.216
on that weaselly son of a bitch,
and do it before 7:00 tonight.

11:11.251 --> 11:13.585
Because if I can't get
enough votes before then,

11:13.637 --> 11:16.755
the only way we win is to make
this whole thing go away.

11:16.757 --> 11:19.007
<i><font color="#D900D9">[dramatic music]</font></i>

11:19.059 --> 11:20.425
Cancel my day.

11:28.044 --> 11:29.711
We have to talk.

11:29.764 --> 11:31.029
I'm studying, Grammy.

11:31.065 --> 11:32.681
I don't care what you say
you're doing.

11:32.716 --> 11:34.383
What I say I'm doing?

11:34.418 --> 11:36.301
Father Walker called me.

11:36.353 --> 11:37.453
He said you've been
acting out.

11:37.488 --> 11:38.854
Father Walker's a priest.

11:38.889 --> 11:40.322
He thinks you're acting out
if you're chewing gum.

11:40.357 --> 11:41.657
Well, I agree with him.

11:41.692 --> 11:43.659
Yeah, and you're not at school
and all I do is get As.

11:43.694 --> 11:45.227
I don't care
what you're getting.

11:45.262 --> 11:46.295
I found these in the trash.

11:46.330 --> 11:47.629
So what.

11:47.665 --> 11:48.864
So what?

11:48.899 --> 11:50.866
"The Little Prince,"
"James and the Giant Peach,"

11:50.901 --> 11:52.468
Michael, you love these books.

11:52.503 --> 11:53.702
Yeah, when I was a kid.

11:53.754 --> 11:55.137
Those books were your
connection to your mother

11:55.172 --> 11:56.638
and father.

11:56.674 --> 12:00.542
Yeah, well,
I don't want them anymore.

12:00.544 --> 12:01.977
You don't want
this one either?

12:01.979 --> 12:04.580
Your mother and I
didn't always get along,

12:04.615 --> 12:07.499
but I know that she read this
to you every night

12:07.551 --> 12:09.685
when you were little
because she told me.

12:09.687 --> 12:13.355
And I also know that you'd
never let me read it to you

12:13.390 --> 12:16.058
because you said
it was so special.

12:16.093 --> 12:17.626
Like I said,
I'm not a kid anymore.

12:17.661 --> 12:18.961
Michael,
I'm worried about you.

12:18.996 --> 12:20.496
Father Walker is worried.

12:20.531 --> 12:22.097
I don't care what
Father Walker thinks,

12:22.132 --> 12:25.400
and I don't care about
these stupid books.

12:25.436 --> 12:27.703
Well, I do care,

12:27.738 --> 12:29.938
and I think you'd better go talk
to Father Walker tomorrow

12:29.990 --> 12:32.474
because you're not
getting all As.

12:32.510 --> 12:36.545
He's giving you an F
on your history paper.

12:39.617 --> 12:41.717
Louis, what are you
doing here?

12:41.752 --> 12:43.151
How did you get past Stacy?

12:43.187 --> 12:44.353
I walked right by her.

12:44.388 --> 12:46.221
Well, in that case,
what can I do for you?

12:46.257 --> 12:48.690
I want to know what the hell
you have on Jack Soloff.

12:48.726 --> 12:50.959
I have nothing on Jack
other than his trust

12:50.995 --> 12:53.579
and confidence that I'm
a better attorney than Jessica.

12:53.631 --> 12:54.563
Shut your mouth.

12:54.598 --> 12:55.864
You're not fit to
lick her boots.

12:55.900 --> 12:58.433
Good, because that's
your job, Louis, not mine.

12:58.469 --> 13:00.602
Listen to me.

13:00.638 --> 13:01.970
Remember when I told you
I'd kill you

13:02.006 --> 13:04.423
if you so much as tell me
the incorrect time?

13:04.475 --> 13:05.674
Tell me what you have
on Jack right now

13:05.726 --> 13:06.942
or you're dead
in 15 seconds.

13:06.977 --> 13:08.610
I remember when
you did that, Louis.

13:08.646 --> 13:11.346
And right after that,
I went straight to my attorneys

13:11.382 --> 13:14.616
and told them
you had threatened my life.

13:14.652 --> 13:17.519
And now, you've come into
my office and done it again

13:17.555 --> 13:18.487
in front of a witness.

13:18.522 --> 13:20.055
What witness?

13:20.090 --> 13:21.657
Stacy, did you get that?

13:21.692 --> 13:23.258
<i>I got it.</i>

13:23.310 --> 13:24.526
So as I see it,

13:24.562 --> 13:27.429
security will be here
in about 60 seconds.

13:27.464 --> 13:29.948
So if you want to kill me,

13:29.984 --> 13:31.583
now is your chance.

13:31.635 --> 13:32.935
I swear to God,
I will find out

13:32.970 --> 13:34.202
what you're holding
over Jack's head.

13:34.238 --> 13:35.537
I doubt that,

13:35.573 --> 13:37.573
and I certainly doubt that
you'll find it by 7:00.

13:37.608 --> 13:39.558
So instead of me telling you
what I have on Jack,

13:39.593 --> 13:40.909
let me tell you
what I have on you.

13:40.945 --> 13:42.377
You vote with me today

13:42.413 --> 13:44.680
and your sister's company
lives.

13:44.715 --> 13:45.948
- What?
- Oh, it turns out

13:45.983 --> 13:48.350
my client is looking to get into
the muffin business.

13:48.385 --> 13:49.952
You leave my sister
out of this.

13:49.987 --> 13:51.486
Sure thing.

13:51.522 --> 13:53.388
As long as you vote
to remove Jessica.

13:53.424 --> 13:55.090
I can't do that.

13:55.125 --> 13:57.459
Then I'm not only
gonna buy it,

13:57.494 --> 14:00.262
I'm gonna rip that company
of hers apart.

14:00.314 --> 14:01.897
You son of a bitch!
She never did anything to you.

14:01.932 --> 14:03.632
No.

14:03.667 --> 14:04.600
But you did.

14:04.635 --> 14:06.368
And Jessica did.

14:06.403 --> 14:08.637
And Harvey did.

14:08.672 --> 14:11.073
So you have a choice,

14:11.108 --> 14:14.309
your firm or your family.

14:23.721 --> 14:25.687
Michael?

14:25.739 --> 14:27.656
<i>It's been a long time.</i>

14:27.691 --> 14:29.591
People have been calling me
that a lot lately.

14:29.627 --> 14:33.061
Maybe it's a sign.

14:33.097 --> 14:34.696
How can I help you?

14:34.732 --> 14:36.848
I need to talk to someone.

14:36.900 --> 14:40.118
I was hoping to do it
under the confessional.

14:40.170 --> 14:42.004
How long has it been
since your last confession?

14:42.039 --> 14:43.839
Aren't you supposed to
ask me that after we started?

14:43.874 --> 14:44.840
We have started.

14:44.875 --> 14:47.492
Have a seat.

14:47.544 --> 14:48.710
Here?

14:48.746 --> 14:49.845
Why not?

14:49.880 --> 14:51.680
Confession's meant to be
good for the soul

14:51.715 --> 14:53.382
and no one's ever said anything
about it having to be done

14:53.417 --> 14:56.051
in a little dark box.

14:56.086 --> 14:58.387
Please.

14:59.890 --> 15:01.657
You gave that paper
an F?

15:01.692 --> 15:03.058
It deserves an A.

15:03.093 --> 15:05.127
What about the fact that
you cut the entire afternoon

15:05.162 --> 15:06.728
last Tuesday?
I had a doctor's appointment.

15:06.764 --> 15:08.063
You even had a note
from your grandmother.

15:08.098 --> 15:09.297
That's right, I did.

15:09.299 --> 15:10.465
The problem is, Michael,

15:10.501 --> 15:12.334
your grandmother wrote me
a note yesterday

15:12.369 --> 15:14.469
thanking me for letting
her book club use the library.

15:14.505 --> 15:17.139
And those two signatures,

15:17.174 --> 15:20.042
they don't look the same
at all.

15:22.279 --> 15:23.412
Okay, well, if you're
so sure I did this,

15:23.447 --> 15:24.847
then why are you
only giving me an F

15:24.898 --> 15:26.581
and not suspending me?

15:26.617 --> 15:28.250
Because I don't think
it's a coincidence that

15:28.285 --> 15:30.919
you chose to cut class on
parent-teacher conference day.

15:30.954 --> 15:33.088
That had nothing
to do with it.

15:33.123 --> 15:35.357
Mike, your grandmother told me
about the books you threw out.

15:35.409 --> 15:37.042
Every parent in the world
is obsessed

15:37.094 --> 15:38.210
with their kid
cleaning their room.

15:38.262 --> 15:39.344
I actually do it,

15:39.396 --> 15:41.129
and the two of you make
a federal case out of it.

15:41.165 --> 15:42.631
You didn't throw out
those books to clean.

15:42.666 --> 15:44.683
You did it because you saw
those kids out there

15:44.735 --> 15:46.301
with their parents

15:46.336 --> 15:48.403
and you just couldn't
deal with that pain.

15:48.439 --> 15:51.373
So you cut class,
you went home,

15:51.408 --> 15:53.608
and you threw away the books.

15:53.644 --> 15:55.143
You don't know what I did.

15:55.179 --> 15:57.979
What I do know is that your
parents came here every Sunday

15:57.981 --> 16:00.348
and donated money
to pay for that uniform

16:00.384 --> 16:02.517
because they wanted you to
be here getting an education

16:02.519 --> 16:03.769
and not cutting class.

16:03.821 --> 16:05.537
I've gotten a perfect grade
on every assignment

16:05.572 --> 16:07.089
I've ever gotten,
all right?

16:07.124 --> 16:09.057
And I don't need to go to
your stupid class to do it.

16:09.093 --> 16:10.358
I could have suspended you,

16:10.394 --> 16:11.927
and that would have been
much worse than an F.

16:11.962 --> 16:14.196
But you're getting one
or you're getting the other.

16:14.231 --> 16:17.966
So why don't you take
one night off from blaming me,

16:17.968 --> 16:20.769
and you decided what it is
that you're gonna do?

16:21.839 --> 16:22.839
Harvey,

16:22.890 --> 16:23.972
what are you doing here?

16:24.007 --> 16:26.541
I wanted to
ask you something.

16:26.577 --> 16:27.959
I was wondering if
I could stay with you

16:28.011 --> 16:29.728
while I do my clerkship.

16:29.763 --> 16:32.197
You want to stay with me
for the summer?

16:32.232 --> 16:34.032
I promise you won't
even know I'm there.

16:34.068 --> 16:35.417
Are you crazy?

16:35.452 --> 16:37.886
Do you have any idea what the
people around here would think

16:37.888 --> 16:38.987
if they found out?

16:39.022 --> 16:40.505
Who says
they're gonna find out?

16:40.541 --> 16:42.674
I mean, no one knows anything
about your personal life anyway.

16:42.726 --> 16:44.793
Harvey, what's going on?

16:44.828 --> 16:46.094
Things aren't good
at home.

16:46.130 --> 16:47.295
Your brother?

16:47.331 --> 16:48.997
It's my parents.

16:49.032 --> 16:50.532
Listen, Harvey,
I know what it's like

16:50.567 --> 16:52.417
to be living in a home
that's not right,

16:52.469 --> 16:55.337
and I also know that you might
be tempted to fix things.

16:55.339 --> 16:57.005
But it's not up to
the children to fix things.

16:57.040 --> 16:59.107
What if it was?

16:59.143 --> 17:00.609
Then there's something wrong
with those two people.

17:00.644 --> 17:02.210
No, there isn't.

17:02.246 --> 17:03.879
There's something wrong
with one of them,

17:03.914 --> 17:08.650
and I don't know whether to
tell the other one or not.

17:08.652 --> 17:12.020
Look, Harvey, I can't
tell you what you should do.

17:12.071 --> 17:15.891
But I can tell you
if you come work for me,

17:15.893 --> 17:18.292
you're gonna have to have
some difficult conversations.

17:18.328 --> 17:19.861
That's work,
this is family.

17:19.896 --> 17:23.799
There are no more difficult
conversations than that.

17:25.219 --> 17:28.386
But for the record,

17:28.422 --> 17:32.007
if you do come work here,

17:32.059 --> 17:36.061
we're gonna be family, too.

17:42.230 --> 17:44.665
Hey there.

17:44.700 --> 17:46.800
Your father and Marcus
will be here any minute,

17:46.836 --> 17:49.236
and, oh, I made your favorite,
chicken parm.

17:49.271 --> 17:50.454
I'm glad they're not here.

17:50.489 --> 17:51.805
It'll give me a chance
to tell you that

17:51.841 --> 17:53.373
I'll pretend
when they're here,

17:53.409 --> 17:55.709
but I am not gonna pretend
when we're alone.

17:55.745 --> 17:58.212
Harvey, please,
I'm still your mother.

17:58.247 --> 17:59.279
No, you're not.

17:59.315 --> 18:01.415
Hey, hey, hey,
look who's here.

18:01.450 --> 18:04.068
I thought you were
working late tonight.

18:04.103 --> 18:05.953
What's up,
douche nozzle?

18:05.988 --> 18:07.988
You remember Bobby from down
at the shop, don't you, Harvey?

18:08.023 --> 18:10.357
<i>He's helping us get</i>
<i>the old Mustang up and running.</i>

18:10.392 --> 18:12.843
That's right, Harvey,
I'm getting the Mustang.

18:12.895 --> 18:14.194
And if you think you're ever
getting behind the wheel

18:14.230 --> 18:15.529
of that car--

18:15.564 --> 18:16.730
I'm never gonna get behind
the wheel of that car.

18:16.766 --> 18:17.781
Because you're jealous.

18:17.833 --> 18:18.832
Because that car's
a piece of shit.

18:18.868 --> 18:21.018
Harvey, watch your mouth.

18:21.053 --> 18:23.771
Lil, do we have enough for
an extra plate?

18:23.806 --> 18:25.339
Sure.
How you doing, Bobby?

18:25.391 --> 18:27.941
I'll be good as soon as
I get this grease off my hands.

18:27.993 --> 18:29.159
Where's the bathroom again?

18:29.211 --> 18:31.411
It's down the hall, Bobby.

18:31.447 --> 18:32.846
You know what?

18:32.882 --> 18:34.131
We don't need an extra plate
'cause I'm not eating.

18:34.166 --> 18:35.649
What are you talking about?
You're home early.

18:35.684 --> 18:36.583
Your mother made
chicken parm.

18:36.619 --> 18:37.885
Well, why don't you eat it?

18:37.920 --> 18:39.853
Because I can't stand
chicken parm anymore.

18:39.889 --> 18:41.638
Where you going?
Harvey!

18:41.690 --> 18:45.192
This is still my house,
you know.

18:45.227 --> 18:47.528
Is it?

18:48.998 --> 18:51.698
So other people know
about you?

18:51.734 --> 18:54.735
Not everyone
knows everything, but...

18:56.038 --> 18:59.156
people know that
I don't have a law degree.

18:59.208 --> 19:02.509
You say that as though
it were just a technicality.

19:02.545 --> 19:04.678
And you say that
as if you're judging me.

19:04.713 --> 19:07.080
Isn't that what you
came here for?

19:07.116 --> 19:08.215
I came here for advice.

19:08.250 --> 19:10.584
You said you came here
to confess.

19:10.619 --> 19:13.153
But it doesn't matter,
because if--

19:13.189 --> 19:14.354
well, if you're looking
for absolution,

19:14.390 --> 19:15.355
I can't give it to you.

19:15.391 --> 19:16.391
Why not?

19:16.425 --> 19:19.760
Because absolution
requires contrition,

19:19.795 --> 19:21.395
and I'm not hearing that
you even think

19:21.430 --> 19:22.629
you've done anything wrong.

19:22.665 --> 19:23.664
Because using my brain
to help people

19:23.699 --> 19:25.132
isn't doing anything wrong.

19:25.134 --> 19:26.834
You're not using
your brain to help people.

19:26.869 --> 19:28.519
You're using it to
fool people,

19:28.554 --> 19:30.838
and you want me to tell you that
you're a good person for it.

19:30.873 --> 19:32.072
I am a good person.

19:32.107 --> 19:33.774
You're a person that
wants to have their cake

19:33.809 --> 19:35.175
and eat it, too.

19:35.211 --> 19:36.743
And I'm afraid that
I'm all out of cake with you.

19:36.779 --> 19:37.945
What is that
supposed to mean?

19:37.980 --> 19:40.247
It means that
I've often wondered

19:40.282 --> 19:41.648
whether or not
I did the right thing

19:41.684 --> 19:43.283
by not having you arrested
that day.

19:43.319 --> 19:45.118
That would have completely
screwed up my life.

19:45.154 --> 19:48.522
Oh, and look at how not
screwed up it is right now.

19:48.557 --> 19:51.024
You want to know
what kind of man I am?

19:51.060 --> 19:53.961
<i><font color="#D900D9">[stirring music]</font></i>

19:53.996 --> 20:01.635
<i>♪
♪</i>

20:01.637 --> 20:03.937
You wanted to see me, Father?

20:03.939 --> 20:07.174
Yes, I did.

20:07.209 --> 20:08.775
I was hoping
you could explain why

20:08.811 --> 20:12.479
we're missing $936
from the collection box.

20:12.514 --> 20:13.814
I can't.

20:13.849 --> 20:17.150
Well, that's odd,
because this box was in my desk,

20:17.186 --> 20:19.920
and I also found this

20:19.955 --> 20:22.155
on my desk.

20:22.191 --> 20:24.458
Michael, the next time
you want to send a message,

20:24.493 --> 20:26.627
just leave me a note.

20:26.662 --> 20:28.528
The uniform's not a message.
I'm just returning it.

20:28.564 --> 20:31.465
You said I had two options,
get an F or get suspended.

20:31.500 --> 20:34.434
But I thought of a third.

20:34.470 --> 20:35.836
So you're dropping out?

20:35.871 --> 20:37.771
No, I'm going to
public school.

20:37.806 --> 20:39.840
And I'm not saying that
I took that cash,

20:39.875 --> 20:41.575
but if I did, I'd be
smart enough to do the math.

20:41.610 --> 20:45.445
My parents put $3 in the
collection plate every week.

20:45.481 --> 20:47.881
$3 a week for 52 weeks
for six years--

20:47.917 --> 20:50.450
$936.

20:50.486 --> 20:53.520
And I would have thought that
belonged to my parents

20:53.572 --> 20:57.457
and I would have just been
taking it back.

20:59.361 --> 21:01.295
You know, I could
have you arrested.

21:01.330 --> 21:02.479
Then do it.

21:02.514 --> 21:03.931
Michael, we both know
how smart you are,

21:03.966 --> 21:06.767
but there's a difference between
intelligence and wisdom.

21:06.802 --> 21:08.502
And if you don't figure
that out eventually,

21:08.537 --> 21:10.170
you're gonna have a lot bigger
problems than an F,

21:10.205 --> 21:11.471
because you can't outsmart--

21:11.507 --> 21:12.406
God?

21:12.441 --> 21:13.607
I know.

21:13.642 --> 21:16.043
I know you don't believe
in God,

21:16.045 --> 21:19.513
so let's just call them...

21:19.548 --> 21:21.348
consequences.

21:21.350 --> 21:22.950
Good-bye, Father.

21:22.985 --> 21:26.420
You want to call the police,
you know where to find me.

21:26.455 --> 21:27.988
Wouldn't be the first time

21:28.040 --> 21:32.025
they came to give Grammy
some bad news.

21:35.764 --> 21:37.164
You never spent it.

21:37.199 --> 21:40.801
Not a penny.

21:46.675 --> 21:48.725
Get out.

21:48.761 --> 21:51.495
Hey, get out!
Harvey, you and me are going.

21:51.547 --> 21:53.513
<i>Right now.</i>

21:53.549 --> 21:54.781
No, we're not.

21:54.817 --> 21:55.949
Yes, we are.

21:55.985 --> 21:59.002
And it's happening whether
you like it or not.

21:59.038 --> 22:01.805
Oh.

22:01.840 --> 22:03.357
Now, you wanna tell me
what was going on

22:03.409 --> 22:04.941
with that bullshit
back at the house?

22:04.994 --> 22:06.660
What bullshit?

22:06.695 --> 22:08.195
I wasn't hungry
so I just left.

22:08.230 --> 22:09.563
I'm not buying it.

22:09.598 --> 22:10.580
I know something's up
with you.

22:10.616 --> 22:11.498
Nothing's up.

22:11.550 --> 22:12.499
Nothing?

22:12.551 --> 22:14.801
<font color="#D900D9">[both grunting]</font>

22:14.853 --> 22:16.820
Your little brother was
excited to see you

22:16.855 --> 22:18.522
and you didn't give him
the time of day.

22:18.574 --> 22:20.540
Marcus was excited
to get Bobby's car.

22:20.576 --> 22:22.426
Since when you got
something against Bobby?

22:22.461 --> 22:23.577
He never did anything to you.

22:23.612 --> 22:26.697
Just let it go, Dad.

22:26.732 --> 22:27.914
Since when do I do that?

22:27.966 --> 22:30.017
Since when were you
around not to?

22:30.052 --> 22:33.620
Excuse me?

22:33.655 --> 22:36.023
I said let it go.

22:36.058 --> 22:37.991
I'm not letting it go!

22:38.027 --> 22:40.527
You disrespected me,

22:40.562 --> 22:42.429
and you disrespected
your brother and your mother

22:42.431 --> 22:43.897
and our guest.

22:43.899 --> 22:46.249
Now, I know
something's up with you.

22:46.301 --> 22:49.202
I want to know what it is.

22:49.238 --> 22:50.203
It's nothing.

22:50.239 --> 22:51.405
It's not nothing!

22:51.440 --> 22:53.040
Why are you doing this?

22:53.075 --> 22:55.042
'Cause there's something
wrong with my boy.

22:55.094 --> 22:58.078
<font color="#D900D9">[groans]</font>

23:00.549 --> 23:02.182
Something's wrong with me?

23:02.217 --> 23:03.500
What about you?

23:03.552 --> 23:06.186
How can you not see what is
going on under your nose

23:06.238 --> 23:08.422
in your own goddamn house?

23:08.457 --> 23:10.107
All right.
Son, stop!

23:10.142 --> 23:12.492
I told her to stop,
but I shouldn't have had to.

23:12.528 --> 23:13.593
It's shouldn't have been me!

23:13.629 --> 23:15.128
Aah!

23:15.164 --> 23:18.532
<i><font color="#D900D9">[dark music]</font></i>

23:18.567 --> 23:21.401
I'm sorry.

23:21.437 --> 23:24.471
I'm so sorry.

23:24.473 --> 23:27.808
You told her to stop what?

23:27.860 --> 23:31.845
<i>What was your mother doing?</i>

23:31.880 --> 23:34.247
Bobby.

23:34.283 --> 23:41.922
<i>♪
♪</i>

23:41.957 --> 23:43.957
So your parents' marriage
ended?

23:43.959 --> 23:45.725
It should have
ended sooner.

23:45.727 --> 23:47.060
Harvey, I'm not
defending your mother,

23:47.096 --> 23:48.712
but what if you'd kept
that promise

23:48.747 --> 23:49.796
and then she broke it off
with Bobby?

23:49.832 --> 23:50.931
What difference
does it make?

23:50.966 --> 23:52.132
Well, the difference is

23:52.167 --> 23:53.366
you didn't have to tell
your father like that.

23:53.402 --> 23:55.168
Yeah, I told him like that
because I had no choice.

23:55.204 --> 23:57.137
No, no, no, no, telling him
like that was your choice.

23:57.172 --> 23:58.371
He was attacking me.

23:58.407 --> 23:59.673
<i>Well, you could have</i>
<i>dropped your guard.</i>

23:59.708 --> 24:00.740
I wasn't gonna do that.

24:00.776 --> 24:02.275
- He was your father.
- I don't care!

24:02.311 --> 24:03.343
Why?

24:03.345 --> 24:05.195
Because I don't lay down!

24:05.230 --> 24:08.281
And instead of
telling him gently

24:08.333 --> 24:10.617
and making a decision calmly,

24:10.669 --> 24:12.285
you hurt your father
even more.

24:12.287 --> 24:13.620
What are you saying?

24:13.672 --> 24:16.123
I'm saying that maybe
you're remembering this story

24:16.125 --> 24:18.792
to tell yourself that
your decision with Forstman

24:18.844 --> 24:20.794
isn't about laying down.

24:20.846 --> 24:23.847
It's about something more.

24:29.097 --> 24:31.965
Hey, baby.

24:34.253 --> 24:35.836
You're never going to
believe this.

24:35.888 --> 24:39.973
Harvey asked if he could
live with me today.

24:40.009 --> 24:41.808
I'm surprised
you didn't say yes.

24:41.844 --> 24:43.577
What?

24:43.629 --> 24:45.128
<i>You already live</i>
<i>at the office.</i>

24:45.164 --> 24:47.014
<i>Why not just</i>
<i>bring it home with you?</i>

24:47.049 --> 24:49.316
Quentin, I told you,

24:49.351 --> 24:51.952
you mean more to me
than work.

24:51.987 --> 24:54.021
Well, actions speak louder
than words.

24:54.056 --> 24:55.422
I married you.

24:55.457 --> 24:56.857
- You did.
- Mm-hmm.

24:56.892 --> 24:59.726
But does Harvey or anyone else
at the office know that?

24:59.762 --> 25:01.628
Or even know that I exist?

25:01.664 --> 25:04.448
You know
I'm a private person.

25:04.483 --> 25:07.167
I like to keep those parts
of my life separate.

25:07.202 --> 25:09.136
What I know is, separate
but equal didn't work out there,

25:09.171 --> 25:10.537
and it's not working
in here.

25:10.572 --> 25:12.239
Where are you going
with this?

25:12.274 --> 25:14.141
You know where
this is going, Jessica,

25:14.176 --> 25:17.010
where it's been going
for a long time.

25:17.046 --> 25:19.947
I want a divorce.

25:19.982 --> 25:21.481
What?

25:21.517 --> 25:23.150
This isn't working anymore.

25:23.185 --> 25:26.320
Does this have
anything to do with Lisa?

25:26.355 --> 25:28.388
No.
This has to do with us.

25:28.424 --> 25:30.324
Oh, you mean me.

25:30.326 --> 25:31.541
I do.

25:31.593 --> 25:35.629
Now you can focus on what
really matters to you...

25:35.664 --> 25:37.664
your career.

25:37.700 --> 25:40.550
<i><font color="#D900D9">[dark music]</font></i>

25:40.602 --> 25:48.342
<i>♪
♪</i>

25:51.714 --> 25:53.964
Jessica,
can I talk to you?

25:54.016 --> 25:56.116
I take it
you haven't found out

25:56.151 --> 25:57.617
what Hardman has on Jack.

25:57.653 --> 25:58.952
I haven't,
but there's something else.

25:58.988 --> 26:01.338
Doesn't matter.

26:01.390 --> 26:02.889
I got us the votes.

26:02.925 --> 26:04.291
You did?

26:04.326 --> 26:06.393
I went to Paul Porter
and I turned him

26:06.428 --> 26:08.929
and the three votes that
he comes with.

26:08.964 --> 26:10.197
So we're up by three?

26:10.232 --> 26:13.133
No, including Harvey,
we're up by one.

26:13.168 --> 26:14.901
No, we're not.

26:14.937 --> 26:17.237
Hardman's going after
Esther's company.

26:17.272 --> 26:21.274
And he's not going to back off
unless you vote against me.

26:22.444 --> 26:23.660
Louis--

26:23.696 --> 26:25.028
I know what you're gonna say.
We can stop it.

26:25.080 --> 26:27.914
But I went to Jeffrey to get him
to not sell his shares,

26:27.950 --> 26:30.417
and he told me that Hardman's
offering 40% over asking.

26:30.452 --> 26:33.086
Jeffrey agreed not to sell,
but everyone else will.

26:33.122 --> 26:36.039
If Hardman can't get the stocks,
he's gonna buy the distributor,

26:36.091 --> 26:37.290
and if he can't buy
the distributor,

26:37.292 --> 26:38.625
he's gonna go after
the contracts.

26:38.627 --> 26:39.760
Louis--

26:39.795 --> 26:41.011
Forstman is his backer!

26:41.046 --> 26:44.047
I know.

26:49.388 --> 26:52.472
Well then, you know that
he has unlimited resources,

26:52.524 --> 26:54.307
and I can't fight a war
on multiple fronts.

26:54.360 --> 26:56.193
And I could tell you that
if you side with me,

26:56.228 --> 26:58.478
we'll figure out a way
to save Esther's company.

26:58.480 --> 27:00.897
But I have a sister, too.

27:00.949 --> 27:02.566
I'm sorry.

27:02.618 --> 27:04.234
Louis...

27:04.286 --> 27:07.571
<i><font color="#D900D9">[stirring music]</font></i>

27:07.623 --> 27:10.157
Whatever happens,

27:10.209 --> 27:15.212
I want you to know...

27:15.247 --> 27:18.799
Pearson will always
consider Litt

27:18.834 --> 27:21.468
her partner.

27:21.503 --> 27:29.509
<i>♪
♪</i>

27:45.527 --> 27:53.533
<i>♪
♪</i>

27:53.535 --> 27:55.535
Jessica.

27:55.537 --> 27:58.872
If it had been anybody
other than his sister,

27:58.924 --> 28:00.373
he would never even consider--

28:00.426 --> 28:02.042
<i>I know, Donna.</i>

28:02.044 --> 28:04.511
And you don't have to
apologize for him

28:04.546 --> 28:07.380
because I know what a bastard
Daniel Hardman is.

28:07.382 --> 28:10.717
Is there anything
I can do?

28:12.554 --> 28:13.637
Yes.

28:13.689 --> 28:16.690
We still have some time
before the vote.

28:19.728 --> 28:22.446
I asked Gretchen to find Harvey
this morning.

28:22.481 --> 28:25.482
I asked the wrong person.

28:27.953 --> 28:30.320
I'll find him.

28:30.372 --> 28:37.377
<i>♪
♪</i>

28:40.466 --> 28:41.548
I knew this was a mistake.

28:41.583 --> 28:42.916
I never should have come here.

28:42.918 --> 28:44.251
Michael, you didn't
actually have to come here.

28:44.303 --> 28:45.418
I already knew your story.

28:45.420 --> 28:46.419
Trevor came to see me
six months ago.

28:46.421 --> 28:47.804
Yeah, I know that.

28:47.840 --> 28:49.473
Yeah, but you didn't know
he spent most of that time

28:49.508 --> 28:51.475
talking about you or the fact
that he blames himself

28:51.510 --> 28:52.809
for everything that
happened to you.

28:52.845 --> 28:54.427
Well, maybe he should.

28:54.429 --> 28:55.762
Maybe you should blame
yourself.

28:55.764 --> 28:56.763
Right, and maybe I should
blame myself

28:56.815 --> 28:58.398
for every earthquake
or every war.

28:58.433 --> 28:59.900
That's enough of the vanity,
okay, Michael.

28:59.935 --> 29:01.601
- Vanity?
- Yeah, vanity, self-indulgence,

29:01.637 --> 29:04.104
whatever you want to call
feeling sorry for yourself

29:04.139 --> 29:05.405
ever since that night...
How dare you.

29:05.457 --> 29:06.773
Because that's exactly why
you're in this position

29:06.808 --> 29:08.225
right now.
No!

29:08.260 --> 29:09.476
I'm in this position because
Trevor put me in this position.

29:09.511 --> 29:10.710
No, Michael, no.

29:10.746 --> 29:12.012
That's the difference
between you and Trevor.

29:12.047 --> 29:13.980
He's actually accepted that
his choices were his own,

29:14.032 --> 29:15.248
which means he actually
wants to change his life.

29:15.250 --> 29:16.650
You think I don't want
to change?

29:16.685 --> 29:17.717
Why the hell
do you think I'm here?

29:17.753 --> 29:18.735
I don't know.
Why are you here?

29:18.787 --> 29:20.120
I told you, I want advice.

29:20.172 --> 29:21.721
No, no, people do not need the
protection of the confessional

29:21.723 --> 29:22.889
to get advice.

29:22.925 --> 29:24.124
I did that to protect you.

29:24.126 --> 29:25.458
No, you did that
to protect you.

29:25.494 --> 29:26.927
So you tell me right now,
why are you here?

29:26.962 --> 29:28.578
- It's not that simple.
- It is that simple.

29:28.630 --> 29:30.230
- I can't.
- Why are you here?

29:30.265 --> 29:33.149
Because I'm afraid!

29:36.872 --> 29:39.739
<i><font color="#D900D9">[poignant music]</font></i>

29:39.775 --> 29:41.007
<i>♪
♪</i>

29:41.043 --> 29:44.911
What are you afraid of,
Michael?

29:44.947 --> 29:48.415
They left me all alone.

29:48.450 --> 29:52.219
And now you've found someone
who loves you...

29:54.356 --> 29:57.857
and if you stop being
who you are,

29:57.893 --> 30:01.561
you're afraid
she'll abandon you, too.

30:01.563 --> 30:05.649
What am I gonna do, Father?

30:05.701 --> 30:08.034
Come with me, Michael.

30:08.070 --> 30:10.954
I want to show you something.

30:10.989 --> 30:13.990
<i>♪
♪</i>

30:21.642 --> 30:23.794
Why'd you tell him?

30:23.829 --> 30:25.212
He needed to know.

30:25.247 --> 30:27.881
What he needed was
for us to be a family.

30:27.916 --> 30:29.716
Families aren't built
on lies.

30:29.752 --> 30:31.051
Well, now all we are
is built on shit

30:31.086 --> 30:33.086
because nobody's happy about
what you did except for you.

30:33.122 --> 30:34.154
I didn't do this for me.

30:34.156 --> 30:35.222
You couldn't stand that

30:35.257 --> 30:36.857
I was about to have them
all to myself.

30:36.859 --> 30:38.392
You think I did this to
take something away from you?

30:38.427 --> 30:41.128
You did take something
away from me.

30:41.163 --> 30:42.095
You don't get it.

30:42.131 --> 30:43.764
You get to go back
to law school,

30:43.799 --> 30:44.999
and you're gonna pass the bar,

30:45.034 --> 30:46.900
and you're gonna go live
your big hotshot life,

30:46.935 --> 30:48.402
and I'm gonna be stuck here
on my own.

30:48.437 --> 30:50.404
- You're not on your own.
- Really?

30:50.439 --> 30:52.656
I don't know if you noticed,
but Mom just left

30:52.691 --> 30:57.044
and Dad's not coming out of
his room, so who's here for me?

30:57.079 --> 30:59.880
Hmm?

31:01.650 --> 31:05.819
So two weeks later
I got a place in the city,

31:05.854 --> 31:07.421
I moved out,
and I never went back.

31:07.456 --> 31:08.989
You left your brother
and your father alone

31:09.024 --> 31:10.123
after all that?

31:10.159 --> 31:11.124
I didn't want to.

31:11.160 --> 31:12.292
Then why did you?

31:12.327 --> 31:13.960
Because I couldn't
take knowing that

31:13.996 --> 31:16.930
I was the one that
tore everything to pieces.

31:16.965 --> 31:19.066
And you think you'll be
doing that again if you resign?

31:19.101 --> 31:21.234
I will be doing that again
if I resign.

31:21.270 --> 31:22.869
Well, I think
stepping down

31:22.905 --> 31:25.038
isn't tearing everything
to pieces.

31:25.074 --> 31:27.274
I think it's a chance to
keep everything together.

31:27.309 --> 31:29.876
She gave me my start.

31:29.912 --> 31:32.679
Harvey, I once commented
that Jessica sounds like

31:32.714 --> 31:33.714
a hell of a woman,

31:33.749 --> 31:36.817
and you said,
"What does it matter?"

31:36.852 --> 31:38.385
Well, you're the one
who led me to believe

31:38.420 --> 31:39.636
she's a hell of a woman.

31:39.688 --> 31:40.887
Maybe you did it
for a reason.

31:40.923 --> 31:42.322
What reason?

31:42.357 --> 31:43.990
For me to suggest that
maybe she'll understand

31:44.026 --> 31:46.493
that you leaving doesn't mean
that you don't care about her.

31:46.528 --> 31:48.145
It means that you do.

31:48.197 --> 31:50.263
And what if that's not why
I told you all this?

31:50.299 --> 31:51.965
What if you're wrong?

31:52.000 --> 31:54.167
Then I'll be wrong.

31:54.203 --> 31:56.636
And you'll be able to
handle that.

31:57.973 --> 32:00.173
I spent a lot of time here.

32:00.209 --> 32:01.975
You remember this place?

32:02.010 --> 32:03.777
I remember everything.

32:03.812 --> 32:05.378
I know you do, Michael.

32:05.414 --> 32:07.964
I was always aware of
what a special child you were.

32:08.016 --> 32:09.633
Hasn't changed a bit.

32:09.685 --> 32:11.301
Hasn't it?

32:11.353 --> 32:12.853
What are you talking about?

32:12.905 --> 32:14.354
Michael, I think
you came to see me

32:14.389 --> 32:15.722
because when people
are in crisis

32:15.774 --> 32:18.692
they're searching for
something more,

32:18.727 --> 32:20.060
usually something
they've lost.

32:20.095 --> 32:22.295
I lost my parents,
and I'm not getting them back.

32:22.331 --> 32:25.265
No, Michael,
you lost your faith.

32:28.770 --> 32:31.771
<i><font color="#D900D9">[gentle music]</font></i>

32:31.773 --> 32:39.779
<i>♪
♪</i>

32:44.119 --> 32:46.203
Grammy.

32:46.255 --> 32:48.538
<i>The day after</i>
<i>you left school</i>

32:48.590 --> 32:50.423
<i>she gave me the money back.</i>

32:50.459 --> 32:53.293
Her only request was that
we use some of it

32:53.295 --> 32:56.796
to buy this bookcase

32:56.849 --> 32:58.682
to keep these books
together.

32:58.717 --> 33:00.884
They're my father's books.

33:00.936 --> 33:02.552
<i>And your mother's.</i>

33:02.604 --> 33:05.555
<i><font color="#D900D9">[melancholy music]</font></i>

33:05.607 --> 33:13.613
<i>♪
♪</i>

33:16.318 --> 33:19.486
<i>I never knew</i>
<i>why she did it.</i>

33:19.538 --> 33:21.371
<i>And now I do.</i>

33:21.406 --> 33:22.873
<font color="#D900D9">[crying]</font>

33:22.908 --> 33:26.626
<i>Michael, if you're worried</i>
<i>about Rachel leaving you,</i>

33:26.662 --> 33:28.378
<i>if you stop doing</i>
<i>what you're doing,</i>

33:28.413 --> 33:31.464
<i>I don't think she will.</i>

33:31.500 --> 33:33.633
How do you know?

33:33.669 --> 33:36.336
<i>♪
♪</i>

33:36.338 --> 33:38.171
<font color="#D900D9">[cries]</font>

33:38.173 --> 33:40.140
'Cause I have faith.

33:40.175 --> 33:48.148
<i>♪
♪</i>

33:48.183 --> 33:50.183
<font color="#D900D9">[door opens]</font>

33:50.235 --> 33:51.935
Can I help you?

33:51.987 --> 33:54.237
I was just--

33:54.273 --> 33:55.322
Where is he?

33:55.357 --> 33:57.107
Where is who?

33:57.159 --> 34:00.026
Harvey.

34:00.028 --> 34:01.578
Please, it's an emergency.

34:01.613 --> 34:04.331
Well, I'm sorry,
he's not here,

34:04.366 --> 34:06.032
and I'm afraid I don't know
where he went.

34:06.034 --> 34:08.868
I'm sorry, I just--

34:08.870 --> 34:11.004
Do you mind if I just
sit here for a minute?

34:11.039 --> 34:13.373
Of course.

34:13.375 --> 34:15.609
<font color="#D900D9">[sighs]</font>

34:15.643 --> 34:17.177
You probably know more about
what's going on that I do,

34:17.212 --> 34:18.311
don't you?

34:18.347 --> 34:21.114
I'm sorry,
I can't respond to that.

34:21.149 --> 34:24.951
As long as I'm here...

34:24.987 --> 34:26.186
thank you.

34:26.221 --> 34:27.987
For what?

34:28.023 --> 34:29.489
A few weeks ago
Harvey finally forgave me

34:29.524 --> 34:30.956
for going to Louis.

34:30.993 --> 34:32.391
And I know he never
would have done that

34:32.427 --> 34:33.627
if he hadn't come to see you.

34:33.661 --> 34:35.094
I'm sorry, I can't respond
to that either.

34:35.130 --> 34:37.464
You just did.

34:37.498 --> 34:39.565
And thank you again for
what you're thinking.

34:39.601 --> 34:41.268
And what is that?

34:41.303 --> 34:42.518
That he never would have
come to see you

34:42.554 --> 34:44.871
if it hadn't been for me.

34:44.906 --> 34:46.572
You really can do that.

34:46.608 --> 34:48.507
Yeah, I can.

34:51.597 --> 34:54.898
In fact, I can tell you
what you're thinking right now.

34:54.933 --> 34:56.916
What is that?

34:56.969 --> 34:59.986
You're thinking two things,
actually.

35:01.923 --> 35:07.093
One, this woman would make
an excellent therapist.

35:07.129 --> 35:10.413
And two...

35:10.449 --> 35:13.266
Harvey has no idea
what he's missing.

35:13.302 --> 35:16.086
<i><font color="#D900D9">[poignant music]</font></i>

35:16.121 --> 35:18.405
<i>♪
♪</i>

35:18.440 --> 35:21.941
Well, it seems
Harvey won't be joining us,

35:21.977 --> 35:23.610
so we may as well get started.

35:23.645 --> 35:27.147
We're here because
there's a concern

35:27.182 --> 35:31.835
that I no longer have the best
interests of the firm at heart

35:31.870 --> 35:35.555
but am instead focused
on the selfish interests

35:35.557 --> 35:37.774
of certain individuals.

35:37.809 --> 35:39.225
For those of you
who feel that way,

35:39.261 --> 35:41.394
there's not much I could do

35:41.446 --> 35:43.713
at this point
to change your minds.

35:43.749 --> 35:48.735
So...I'll say...

35:48.770 --> 35:52.505
I hope it remains my pleasure to
serve this firm.

35:52.541 --> 35:54.874
I think it's time we vote.

35:54.926 --> 35:57.177
Well, if you're not gonna say
anything to change their mind,

35:57.229 --> 35:58.678
then I will.

35:58.714 --> 36:00.647
You made it.

36:00.682 --> 36:02.599
Wouldn't have missed it
for the world.

36:02.651 --> 36:04.334
Okay, fine, you're here,

36:04.369 --> 36:06.086
but there's nothing that says
you can plead her case.

36:06.121 --> 36:07.187
And there's nothing
that says he can't,

36:07.222 --> 36:08.588
so why don't you
sit your ass down?

36:08.623 --> 36:10.590
Go ahead, then,
get your speech over with

36:10.625 --> 36:12.125
so we can get to the vote.

36:12.160 --> 36:13.460
No speech, just this.

36:13.495 --> 36:15.495
A termination letter.

36:15.547 --> 36:18.365
As of now, the company that's
been targeting our clients

36:18.400 --> 36:20.734
is no longer represented
by Daniel Hardman.

36:20.769 --> 36:22.402
Bullshit.
<i>Go ahead, call him.</i>

36:22.437 --> 36:23.770
Of course,
it might take a while

36:23.805 --> 36:25.555
since you've got to go through
the prison switchboard

36:25.607 --> 36:26.823
to get ahold of him.

36:26.875 --> 36:28.341
<i>Yep, that's right.</i>

36:28.377 --> 36:31.077
That's the kind of man
Jack Soloff and Daniel Hardman

36:31.113 --> 36:34.614
do business with,
one who's already behind bars.

36:34.649 --> 36:36.349
<i>Look, let me be clear.</i>

36:36.385 --> 36:39.586
<i>The attack on this firm was</i>
<i>an attack on me.</i>

36:39.621 --> 36:43.056
<i>Daniel blamed me</i>
<i>for having to leave this firm,</i>

36:43.091 --> 36:47.327
<i>so he was trying to hit me</i>
<i>where it hurt the most,</i>

36:47.362 --> 36:49.329
<i>namely this firm</i>

36:49.381 --> 36:53.933
<i>and my partners</i>
<i>and my friends.</i>

36:53.969 --> 36:55.502
But that's over.

36:55.537 --> 36:57.604
He has no more money,

36:57.639 --> 36:59.839
no more power,
no more friends.

36:59.875 --> 37:03.276
<i>All of you,</i>
<i>you're about to vote on whether</i>

37:03.311 --> 37:05.695
<i>Jessica should continue</i>
<i>running this firm.</i>

37:05.731 --> 37:08.531
<i>Now, I know some of you think</i>
<i>that she's turned a blind eye</i>

37:08.583 --> 37:11.851
<i>to my behavior</i>
<i>and--and the risks I've taken,</i>

37:11.887 --> 37:15.588
<i>but for you to remove her would</i>
<i>be the greatest risk of all.</i>

37:15.624 --> 37:18.374
<i>Because if there's one thing</i>
<i>I know,</i>

37:18.410 --> 37:20.660
<i>it's that Jessica Pearson cares</i>
<i>about this firm</i>

37:20.695 --> 37:22.262
<i>and everyone in it.</i>

37:22.297 --> 37:25.064
Because to her,
we're not just colleagues

37:25.100 --> 37:28.301
or even friends,

37:28.336 --> 37:30.503
we're family.

37:30.539 --> 37:32.472
<i><font color="#D900D9">[tense music]</font></i>

37:32.507 --> 37:33.807
Thank you, Harvey.

37:38.180 --> 37:39.813
Let's vote.

37:39.848 --> 37:42.449
Jessica, I don't think we're
gonna be needing the ballots.

37:42.484 --> 37:45.618
I think everybody knows
where they stand.

37:45.654 --> 37:49.389
All in favor of Jessica staying.

37:49.424 --> 37:56.463
<i>♪
♪</i>

37:56.498 --> 37:58.465
Then I guess everyone here
is happy

37:58.500 --> 38:01.167
keeping things the way they are,
except for one.

38:01.203 --> 38:08.875
<i>♪
♪</i>

38:14.683 --> 38:18.601
I'm glad you're here.
I need to tell you something.

38:18.653 --> 38:20.537
Whatever it is,
it might not matter

38:20.572 --> 38:21.704
after I give you this.

38:21.756 --> 38:23.623
What is it?

38:25.760 --> 38:28.628
Harvey, you didn't just
give me my dream.

38:30.165 --> 38:32.532
You gave me a family.

38:34.102 --> 38:36.302
But I'm gonna have a family
of my own someday,

38:36.338 --> 38:41.374
and I can't have all of this
hanging over their heads.

38:43.445 --> 38:45.879
You're resigning.

38:45.881 --> 38:50.316
I am.

38:50.352 --> 38:54.621
You know, you once asked me
why I hired you,

38:54.656 --> 38:59.959
and I told you it was
because life is like this

38:59.995 --> 39:01.261
and I like this.

39:01.296 --> 39:02.629
Harvey, please,
you can't convince me--

39:02.664 --> 39:04.814
Let me finish.

39:04.866 --> 39:06.866
It was like this

39:06.902 --> 39:11.955
not because of the risk
we're taking.

39:12.007 --> 39:14.240
It's because of who you are.

39:14.276 --> 39:16.009
So you're not disappointed?

39:16.044 --> 39:17.227
Are you kidding me?

39:17.279 --> 39:20.146
After that speech,
if you hadn't done this,

39:20.181 --> 39:22.916
I'd be kicking you out.

39:22.918 --> 39:24.434
And for the record,

39:24.486 --> 39:28.288
you're not the only one who got
more family out of this deal.

39:28.323 --> 39:31.124
<i><font color="#D900D9">[poignant music]</font></i>

39:31.159 --> 39:38.965
<i>♪
♪</i>

39:48.226 --> 39:50.043
You really are
so beautiful.

39:50.078 --> 39:52.045
No one's beautiful in
fluorescent light.

39:52.080 --> 39:53.379
You are.

39:53.415 --> 39:56.749
So how did your mysterious
adventure go?

39:56.785 --> 39:59.152
Did you get
what you needed?

39:59.204 --> 40:01.537
I did.

40:03.658 --> 40:04.991
What's this?

40:04.993 --> 40:06.993
Early wedding present.

40:07.045 --> 40:09.045
Oh, yeah?

40:14.803 --> 40:16.002
Mike, this is--

40:16.004 --> 40:17.720
A copy of my letter
of resignation.

40:17.756 --> 40:19.222
If this is about
the thing with Claire

40:19.257 --> 40:20.974
or the fight that I got into
with my mom--

40:21.009 --> 40:22.342
It's not.

40:22.344 --> 40:25.428
This is about us
starting our life right,

40:25.480 --> 40:26.846
with a clean slate.

40:26.848 --> 40:28.348
You don't have to do this
for me.

40:28.350 --> 40:30.650
I'm not.

40:30.685 --> 40:31.985
I'm doing it for us.

40:32.020 --> 40:33.380
Because as long as
you're with me--

40:33.405 --> 40:35.688
I'm with you.

40:35.740 --> 40:37.660
Well then, let me go say
good-bye to my office,

40:37.692 --> 40:39.492
and let's go home.

40:39.527 --> 40:42.495
<i><font color="#D900D9">[upbeat music]</font></i>

40:42.530 --> 40:50.536
<i>♪
♪</i>

40:58.680 --> 41:01.180
You walked out before we got
a chance to celebrate.

41:01.216 --> 41:03.766
I'm sorry.
It's just been a long day.

41:03.802 --> 41:07.353
Harvey, how exactly did you
get that termination letter

41:07.389 --> 41:09.222
from Forstman?

41:09.224 --> 41:11.391
Let's talk about it
in the morning.

41:11.393 --> 41:12.959
Harvey.

41:12.994 --> 41:16.396
I agreed to step down.

41:16.398 --> 41:17.530
Absolutely not.

41:17.565 --> 41:19.732
You are not going to step down.

41:19.734 --> 41:20.867
<i>It's done.</i>

41:20.902 --> 41:22.568
Nothing's done.

41:22.620 --> 41:27.573
Jessica, please, you've given
up everything for this firm.

41:27.575 --> 41:29.792
It's time someone gave up
something for you.

41:29.828 --> 41:33.246
What if I don't want you
to be the one to do that?

41:33.248 --> 41:36.249
Then forgive me,
because I am.

41:36.251 --> 41:40.086
Good news is,
Mike Ross is leaving.

41:40.088 --> 41:42.138
I never thought
I'd say this,

41:42.173 --> 41:46.142
but at this moment,

41:46.177 --> 41:47.977
that doesn't feel like
good news.

41:48.013 --> 41:56.019
<i>♪
♪</i>

42:00.909 --> 42:01.909
<i>Michael James Ross.</i>

42:01.943 --> 42:03.359
Yes?

42:03.411 --> 42:06.079
You're under arrest for
conspiracy to commit fraud.

